ALAS-2020-1388

Amazon Linux AMI Security Advisory: ALAS-2020-1388
Advisory Release Date: 2020-06-23 06:44 Pacific
Advisory Updated Date: 2020-06-26 04:47 Pacific
Severity: Medium
References: CVE-2018-17407 
Issue Overview:

An issue was discovered in t1_check_unusual_charstring functions in writet1.c files in TeX Live before 2018-09-21. A buffer overflow in the handling of Type 1 fonts allows arbitrary code execution when a malicious font is loaded by one of the vulnerable tools: pdflatex, pdftex, dvips, or luatex. (CVE-2018-17407)


Affected Packages:

texlive


Issue Correction:
Run yum update texlive to update your system.
